definitions.definition: To do with separation; In, into. [from before 1150]
To do with time; Each, per, in, on, by. Often occurs between two nouns, where the first noun occurs at the end of a verbal phrase. [from before 1150]
examples: I brush my teeth twice a day.

definitions.definition: To do with status; In. [from before 1150]
( archaic ) To do with position or direction; In, on, at, by, towards, onto. [from before 1150]
( archaic ) To do with process, with a passive verb; In the course of, experiencing. [from before 1150]
( archaic ) To do with an action, an active verb; Engaged in. [16th c.]
( archaic ) To do with an action/movement; To, into. [16th c.]
( obsolete ) To do with method; In, with. [from before 1150]
( obsolete ) To do with role or capacity; In. [from before 1150]
